Inflation in the  Democratic Republic 
of Congo rose to 19.44 percent as of Oct. 3 from 19.39 percent a
week earlier, the central bank said.  Prices have increased 0.35 percent so far this month, the
Kinshasa-based central bank said on its website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
